column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Sunny to partly cloudy- light NW wind- boating activity. 0.4" of rain yesterday.
Sunny- light SW wind- no recent rain- substantial boating activity
Sunny- light SE wind.  Lake quiet with calm spots- little boating activity- last rain sun. 6/4 (~.6") .
Mostly sunny- but a storm is moving in from the east-east wind light- little boating activity- lake level back to normal- last rain Thursday a.m.
Hazy sun- light NW wind- little boating activity- slight algae bloom started- last rain Monday 7/25-water temp. 75 degrees.
Partly cloudy- light SW wind- little boating activity- last rain 8/7/94- water temp. 72 degrees.
Partly cloudy- SW wind- lake level normal- no rain of significance for 1 week- no algal bloom.
Sunny- light S wind- some green algae on water surface early a.m. last rain on Sunday night 6/30-water temp. 70s. some boating- water and jet ski activity.

Partly cloudy to mostly sunny.  Light SW breeze- no visible algae bloom- water temperature 75 degrees- last rain wed pm 8/7 and early Thursday am 8/8 (heavy with high winds-heavy tree damage in three lakes area) .

Mostly sunny to partly cloudy- light NE breeze- no rain since sun. 8/25- air temps daytime 70's night cooling to 40's. water temp. 70 degrees- lake quiet- no water-skiing or jet skis since weekend- few boaters.
Partly sunny- winds 10 miles per hour- air temperature 73 degrees.
Mostly cloudy- wind 11 mph from southwest- minimal boat traffic. Birds and bald eagle flying overhead.
Mostly sunny- few clouds- wind NNW 7-8 mph- minimal boat activity.
Sunny- few clouds/haze- wind SSW 11mph- a lot of boat traffic on lake this holiday weekend.
Sunny- few clouds- wind SSE 12 mph- no boat traffic- air temp 72 degrees.
Cloudy/Partly sunny; wind NW 8 mph; no boat traffic; air temp 65 degrees; Water surface temp 72.5 degrees; humidity 75%
Sunny- air temp 75 degrees- wind 1-2 mph- no boat traffic.
Sunny and no clouds; air temp 68 degrees; wind 8 mph from the south; no real boat traffic - 1 fisherman and 1 sailboat
Sunny with a few clouds; air temp 70 degrees; wind 8 mph out of southeast; 3 fisherman; water is cloudy and looks like fall turnover is beginning.
Partly cloudy; 66 degrees F; wind 11 - 15mph out of NNW; minor boat activity

Air temperature 66 degrees; cloudy with a little sun peeking out; wind 7 mph out of the ESE; no boat activity. Air temperature 66 degrees; cloudy with a little sun peeking out; wind 7 mph out of the ESE; no boat activity.

Sunny- only a few clouds. 77 degrees F; wind 4 mph out of SSW; minor boat activity. Noticed a green film on Lake surface in the morning - could be a start to the Fall turnover given cooler night time temps.
Sunny- no clouds. Air temp - 81 degrees. Water surface temp 72.4 degrees. Wind calm/1 mph out of the south; minor boat activity.  Turnover in process.
AIR TEMP 81 DEGREES- SUNNY; WIND 6 MPH OUT OF SSW; MODERATE BOAT TRAFFIC
Sunny with only a few clouds; 81 degrees F; Wind out of the west at 0-2 mph; minimal boat activity.
74 degrees sunny; Wind - calm; minimal boat activity - 2 fishermen.
87 degrees F and sunny; wind 8 mph out of the west; minimal boat activity; Note : equipment was recalibrated a few days ago to barametric pressure readings per Fred Knoch.
Mostly cloudy; 71 degrees F; a few sprinkles of rain; winds calm; no boat traffic at all.
Partly sunny; air temperature 71 degrees; wind 10 mph out of SSE. No boat traffic.
Ice completely off Fourmile Lake Ice completely off Fourmile Lake.
73 degrees; mostly cloudy; wind 10 mph S/SE; no boat traffic.
84 degrees air temp; partly cloudy; wind 8-10 mph S/SE; water surface temp 80.4 degrees; minimal boat activity.
70 degrees and sunny; wind 2-3 mph from the south; water surface temp 74 degrees; barefoot waterskier on north side of lake; water level down 6 inches.
Sunny and 76 degree air temp; wind 8 mph out of SE; water surface temp 73 degrees; 2 fishing boats in lake; water level back up to normal after two heavy (1 inch plus) rains.
Air temp 71 degrees; partly cloudy; wind 13 mph SE; no boat activity- water surface temp 67.4 degrees.
Air temp 64 degrees; cloudy + misting; wind 9-10 W NW; 1 boat cruising; water surface temp of 62 degrees.
Air temp 61 degrees; sunny/partly cloudy; wind 7mph west; 4 fishermen + 2 kayakers; water surface temp 60.5 degrees. Maple trees starting to turn colors.

Air temp 64 degrees; sunny with a few clouds; wind from the west at 8 mph; no activity on the lake; water surface temp 67.4 degrees. Lake turnover starting. Air temp 64 degrees; sunny with a few clouds; wind 8 mph from the west; no activity on the lake; water surface temp 67.4 degrees; lake started Fall turnover; maple trees turning color.
Partly sunny; wind out of south at 10mph; two boats on lake - one sail boat.
Sunny with a few clouds; Air Temp 84 degrees;Water surface temp 77.4 degrees; Wind out of the south at 12 mph; 2 boats and one waterskier.
Sunny with air temp of 84 degrees; surface water temp of 80.4 degrees; wind out of north/northwest at 12 + mph; 5 boats and one sailboat on the lake at present. Beautiful day.
Sunny with a few clouds; air temp 75 degrees; surface water temp 74.5 degrees; wind out of south at 6 mph; 6 boats

Sunny with few clouds; air temp 72 degrees; surface water temp 72.3 degrees; wind out of south/south west at 10 mph; 2 boats fishing; starting to see algae along shore of wind swept side of lake; wild rice in bloom and a few geese frequenting the lake.

Sunny - fog just cleared the lake; air temp of 42 degrees; surface water temp of 58.4 degrees; wind - calm; no boats seen; lake turnover beginning !  Heard a couple of sand hill cranes in the wild rice.
Sunny with very few clouds; air temp 53 degrees; surface water temp 62.2 degrees; wind 3 mph out of west; 3 boats; lake turnover in process - surface algae as a result.
